WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.200
This is Shiny Assistant right here and it's a chat interface to begin with,

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:04.500
but I can ask it to do things.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:06.600
I thought it'd be really useful to have a mortgage calculator.

00:00:06.600 --> 00:00:07.900
And that's all I said, just one sentence.

00:00:07.900 --> 00:00:10.200
Build an application which calculates mortgage payments.

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:13.200
So it starts up Shiny live here running in the browser

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:14.600
and we can change these amounts.

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:16.200
We have a mortgage payment calculator.

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:19.100
Now I can put these numbers in the application itself.

00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:22.900
So that's the starting values because these are more realistic starting values.

00:00:22.900 --> 00:00:27.799
Put them there, hit this rerun app button, this play button to rerun it.

00:00:27.799 --> 00:00:31.100
And as you can see, those are now the default starting values.

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:33.299
Hit calculate and there it is.

00:00:33.299 --> 00:00:37.500
Let's say I want to have a plot of the remaining principal and here we go.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:38.700
That's really helpful.

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:40.599
Let's say I want a little bit more detailed information.

00:00:40.599 --> 00:00:42.900
I can ask it to add an amortization table.

00:00:42.900 --> 00:00:44.799
It's going to be 360 payments total.

00:00:44.799 --> 00:00:47.099
Eventually that's going to go all the way down to zero.

00:00:47.099 --> 00:00:48.599
You know, while you could do this by hand,

00:00:48.599 --> 00:00:50.799
you can see that building something like this,

00:00:50.799 --> 00:00:52.299
it won't always get all the details right.

00:00:52.299 --> 00:00:53.099
It's not perfect.

00:00:53.099 --> 00:00:54.700
It might have some bugs in the code,

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:57.799
but it will help you get started on applications like this way,

00:00:57.799 --> 00:00:59.900
way faster than you might otherwise be able to do.

